HEADWORD: Sheepskin
<hw>Sheep"skin`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
skin of a sheep; or, leather prepared from it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A diploma; -- so called because usually written or
printed on parchment prepared from the skin of the sheep.</def>
<mark>[College Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sheepsplit</ent>⟦br⟧
